From: Beast <beast@mono-gateway.local>
Date: Wed, 26 Mar 2026 21:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] arm64: dts: ls1046a: Add USDPAA reserved memory for
 DPDK DMA

Add a 256MB reserved-memory region at 0xc0000000 for DPDK's DMA
buffer pool. The fsl_usdpaa_mainline driver uses this as a genalloc
pool, served to userspace via the DMA_MAP ioctl and mmap.

The address is chosen to be:
 - Above the typical 2GB kernel mapping for 8GB RAM
 - Below the 4GB DMA boundary
 - Non-overlapping with hugepages (which come from system RAM)

On LS1046A with 8GB DDR4, this reduces available system RAM from
8GB to ~7.75GB — acceptable for a dedicated networking appliance.

Signed-off-by: Beast <beast@mono-gateway.local>
---
 data/dtb/mono-gateway-dk.dts | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

This is a DTS patch applied to the Mono Gateway board DTS, not a
kernel source patch. Insert the reserved-memory node between the
"chosen" and "leds" blocks in the root / { } node.

--- a/data/dtb/mono-gateway-dk.dts
+++ b/data/dtb/mono-gateway-dk.dts
@@ -31,6 +31,20 @@
 	chosen {
 		stdout-path = "serial0:115200n8";
 	};
+
+	reserved-memory {
+		#address-cells = <2>;
+		#size-cells = <2>;
+		ranges;
+
+		/* DPDK DMA buffer pool — 256MB contiguous
+		 * Used by fsl_usdpaa_mainline driver for DMA_MAP ioctl.
+		 * Address 0xc000_0000 is below 4GB DMA boundary.
+		 */
+		usdpaa_mem: usdpaa-mem@c0000000 {
+			compatible = "fsl,usdpaa-mem";
+			reg = <0x0 0xc0000000 0x0 0x10000000>;
+			no-map;
+		};
+	};
 
 	leds {
 		compatible = "gpio-leds";
